				\begin{document}$$\hbox{cm}^{-1}$$\end{document} over the duration of a 35 hr growth. After growth, the crystals were characterised with Raman spectroscopy, Atomic Force Microscopy (AFM) and Scanning Electron Microscopy (SEM) to verify the correct phase, size, and homogeneity. Stoichiometry of individual flakes was confirmed with EDS mapping and surface topography was assessed using AFM, Fig. 1. Individual flakes contain small numbers of crystallites and nanowire growths. Apart from these defects, flakes have RMS roughness \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
